And you call yourself a samurai?

13
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,900
What is that next to you?

14
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:23,870
["It's What's On The Inside That Counts"]

15
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:27,200
[Battle Royal Host]

16
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:27,750
Honestly, you're such a pain.

17
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:31,650
How long have you had Sadaharu-kun?

18
00:02:31,650 --> 00:02:36,030
You still haven't established a
master and pet relationship.

19
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,790
Right, Elizabeth?

20
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:43,670
A true bond of trust between a master and
pet must be deeper than the Sea of Japan

21
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:47,960
[Note: Riki Choshu is a professional
wrestler known for his mullet.]

22
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:47,960
and longer than Choshu's mullet.

23
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,500
Right, Elizabeth?

24
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:53,030
What is it, Gintoki?

25
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,950
You aren't going to eat that parfait?

26
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:58,150
If you aren't, would you
mind if Elizabeth had it?

27
00:02:58,150 --> 00:02:59,630
Right, Elizabeth?

28
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:04,060
Yeah... That isn't Elizabeth, is it?

29
00:03:07,850 --> 00:03:12,170
Gintoki, that was a pretty
witty American joke.

30
00:03:12,170 --> 00:03:13,820
I wasn't telling a joke!

31
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,820
And how was that even American?!

32
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:19,860
Hell, that thing's the one
that looks Americanized!

33
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:28,020
["I'm Russianized"]

34
00:03:21,450 --> 00:03:23,650
How would I know that?!

35
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:26,600
[Note: Parody of Nintendo DS]

36
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:26,600
And why are you using a Bentendo
TS to talk to me?!

37
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,460
Use your usual sign!

38
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:31,080
Anyways, are you okay?

39
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:33,380
Did you eat something rotten?

40
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:36,200
Did you eat something off the floor?

41
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:40,550
As you go through life, it is always
possible to find hope lying around...

42
00:03:40,550 --> 00:03:42,160
That's not what I asked.

43
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:44,500
This is bad. Definitely bad.

44
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:47,810
You were bad to begin with, but you've taken
it to a whole new level today, Zura.

45
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,840
It's Katsura, not Zura.

46
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:54,120
In any case, we don't have time
to listen to your foolishness.

47
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,170
Let's go, Elizabeth.

48
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:01,500
Th-Thank you very much...

49
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:04,120
[Note: This is a 10,000 yen bill. 10,000 yen
is equivalent to USD $100.]

50
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,860
Th-Thank you very much.

51
00:04:06,860 --> 00:04:08,160
I'll go get your change.

52
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:10,680
["Keep the change"]

53
00:04:11,230 --> 00:04:14,530
Thank you very much!
Thank you so very much!

54
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:37,430
Elizabeth, you seem to have forgotten
how to use chopsticks.

55
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:40,720
No matter. I'll teach you
from the beginning.

56
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,940
Since we live in a land of chopsticks.

57
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,750
I-Indeed...

58
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:49,870
It's just like Gin-san said.

59
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:51,870
It's no longer the Elizabeth we know.

60
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:54,270
That's no simple makeover.

61
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:56,470
Doesn't even look like a fake.

62
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:57,900
It's something completely different.

63
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:01,060
I wonder what happened
to the real Elizabeth.

64
00:05:01,430 --> 00:05:02,920
Hey now...

65
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:05,330
Why are you getting all gloomy?

66
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:07,050
Why wouldn't we?!

67
00:05:07,990 --> 00:05:11,030
I might not be able to compare
with Katsura-san,

68
00:05:11,030 --> 00:05:14,080
but I have my own share of fond
memories with Elizabeth.

69
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:16,680
Me too!

70
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:20,220
All of the memories are so beautiful.

71
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:22,860
No, there's nothing beautiful about that.

72
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:25,200
And wait, why are you remembering
last night's dinner?

73
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,870
That has nothing to do with Elizabeth.

74
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:30,220
I'll find a way to wake Katsura-san up!

75
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:33,730
Katsura-san will surely be sad when
he realizes what's happened!

76
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:34,730
Right on!

77
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:38,120
That fake can't hold a
candle to Elizabeth!

78
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:43,340
But Zura usually won't listen
to anything we have to say.

79
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:44,470
No choice then...

80
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:46,700
We'll try to wake him up.

81
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:50,310
Excuse me, you two.

82
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:54,120
Why hello there...

83
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,680
What's with you people?

84
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:02,410
Well, we happen to belong
to a pet-loving society.

85
00:06:02,410 --> 00:06:08,400
There's been a rise in the number of people
keeping illegal animals as pets

86
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,570
or stealing other people's pets.

87
00:06:11,570 --> 00:06:12,740
What was that?!

88
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:15,650
Are you implying that I'm one
of those evil villains?!

89
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:18,660
More stupid than evil.

90
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:21,640
No, no, no! That wasn't our intention.

91
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:25,860
We simply wanted to check
if that was really your pet.

92
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:27,610
Please cooperate!

93
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:29,730
I have no choice...

94
00:06:29,730 --> 00:06:31,890
So what am I supposed to do?

95
00:06:31,890 --> 00:06:36,410
Could you start by providing
some form of ID?

96
00:06:36,410 --> 00:06:37,670
For the pet.

97
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:41,030
Uh, it'd be pretty odd for
a pet to have any ID.

98
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:44,190
What?! It does?!

99
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:45,340
Isn't that odd?!

100
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:47,080
Isn't this pretty odd?!

101
00:06:48,410 --> 00:06:49,510
Himeka...

102
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:50,560
Rise...

103
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,070
Hazuki...

104
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:54,830
How many different hostess
clubs have you been to?!

105
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:54,830
[Note: Girls at hostess clubs usually have their own business cards for their customer to call. More business cards implies more hostess clubs.]

106
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:58,220
Elizabeth is so hopeless.

107
00:06:58,220 --> 00:07:01,160
But where did you get those things?

108
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,500
Isn't that obvious?!

109
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:06,410
They came from society's nighttime outlet where
money and the lust of old men come together!

110
00:07:06,410 --> 00:07:08,370
But this is perfect, Gin-san.

111
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:11,550
The normal Elizabeth would
never go to those places.

112
00:07:11,550 --> 00:07:14,010
One more push and Katsura-san
will notice!

113
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:19,310
Now, we'd like you to fill out a
survey concerning your pet.

114
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:24,390
Why are you filling it out?!

115
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:26,130
And it's in Russian?!

116
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,160
Please look at this, Katsura-san!

117
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:33,030
This is the truth of the unknown
organism next to you!

118
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:34,400
Please wake up!

119
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,360
Can your Elizabeth write in Russian?!

120
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:41,260
Is this the Elizabeth you know?!

121
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:46,730
Th-This is...

122
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:51,820
Y-You...

123
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,880
I'm so happy, Elizabeth!

124
00:08:00,690 --> 00:08:01,820
Why?!

125
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:03,540
There's obviously something wrong here!

126
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:06,290
Your Elizabeth can't write in Russian!

127
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:09,790
You've finally gone from someone
who could only write on that sign

128
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:12,360
to someone who can write on paper!

129
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,080
That's your concern?!

130
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,480
This is wonderful...

131
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:20,260
I was starting to get sick of constantly
throwing away signs.

132
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:22,080
He just revealed how he really felt.

133
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:26,610
And why don't you realize that the Elizabeth in that
flashback isn't the one next to you, dumbnuts!

134
00:08:26,610 --> 00:08:28,340
Let us go, Elizabeth!

135
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:30,470
This country has a bright future!

136
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,770
What do we do?

137
00:08:33,770 --> 00:08:35,690
Forget about waking him up...

138
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:38,290
Katsura-san doesn't feel the
slightest hint of doubt.

139
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:39,780
Man...

140
00:08:39,780 --> 00:08:41,190
I give up.

141
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:46,960
There may still be a way.

142
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:52,210
Hey there, big guy.

143
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,710
[Hostess Club SMILE]

144
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,620
What do you want?

145
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:58,430
We've got some cute girls.

146
00:08:58,430 --> 00:09:01,220
Right now, a samurai accompanied
by a pet gets in for half the price.

147
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:02,560
How about it?

148
00:09:03,270 --> 00:09:08,040
A samurai like myself would never have
time to fool around with such women.

149
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,590
Let's go, Elizabeth.

150
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:14,790
Yes, two coming in!

151
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:17,070
Elizabeth...?

152
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,200
Why welcome!

153
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,540
We'll take extra special
care of you today!

154
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:26,140
Enjoy yourselves.

155
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:28,280
Party of two coming in!

156
00:09:35,610 --> 00:09:38,770
Please, you're such a kidder, sir!

157
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:41,210
It's Elizabeth, not sir.

158
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:43,590
What's going on, Shin-chan?

159
00:09:43,590 --> 00:09:47,080
Was that how the thing with
Katsura-san always was?

160
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,310
W-Well, it's a long story...

161
00:09:49,770 --> 00:09:51,900
But this is a great plan, Gin-san.

162
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:55,570
The fake Elizabeth is obviously
a fan of hostess clubs.

163
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:58,260
An obvious difference from the real thing.

164
00:09:58,260 --> 00:10:00,290
Katsura-san should be confused.

165
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:05,510
Th-Then Elizabeth, shall we get going?

166
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:06,660
Oh, Katsura-san?

167
00:10:06,660 --> 00:10:07,940
You're already leaving?

168
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,550
It's so rare of you to come visit.

169
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:12,770
As a citizen who's concerned
about the future of this nation,

170
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:15,530
I have no time to play around.

171
00:10:15,530 --> 00:10:17,580
Let us go, Elizabeth.

172
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:18,750
Excuse me!

173
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:21,620
This customer wants an extension!

174
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:23,320
An extension?!

175
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,100
What are you saying, Elizabeth?!

176
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:30,940
Wh-What's wrong, Elizabeth?

177
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,280
You're not your usual self!

178
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:36,190
That's right, Katsura-san!

179
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:37,700
That's what we've been trying to tell you!

180
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:40,880
This isn't the Elizabeth you know!

181
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:41,720
That's right!

182
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,850
It's a completely different fake!

183
00:10:43,850 --> 00:10:45,700
Wake up already!

184
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:48,790
I understand...

185
00:10:48,790 --> 00:10:51,420
I'll go wash my face to wake myself up!

186
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:53,820
That's not what we meant!

187
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:58,560
No, Elizabeth is Elizabeth
and nothing but Elizabeth.

188
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:01,050
He seemed really disturbed...

189
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:03,720
Did we bring Katsura-san to his senses?

190
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,070
Beats me.

191
00:11:05,070 --> 00:11:10,320
But he should have noticed that
thing isn't Elizabeth by now.

192
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:12,440
Excuse me!

193
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:16,130
This customer wants a bottle
of Dom Perignon Rose!

194
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:16,130
[Note: Often served at Hostess
Clubs at super high price.]

195
00:11:16,130 --> 00:11:20,670
And a fruit plate, a whole ham,
and order out for sushi!

196
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:23,060
Hey! Cut this out already!

197
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:25,310
You're really starting to push it!

198
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:25,990
Hey!

199
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:28,370
You're already running one scam
by pretending to be Elizabeth,

200
00:11:28,370 --> 00:11:30,330
and now you're going to gorge
yourself without paying!

201
00:11:30,330 --> 00:11:32,060
This bastard's an appetite robber!

202
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:35,940
If you're gonna drink that much, you should
be buying us a round, fake Elizabeth!

203
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:39,050
[Order whatever you want]

204
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,180
[Why don't YOU play around in grand style?]
[Note: Impersonating Johnny Kitagawa, the founder and former president of Johnny & Associates, a famous male talent agency.]

205
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:44,570
Uh, but...

206
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:52,600
Woo-hoo!

207
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:00,350
You're such an animal, champ!

208
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:03,130
You're incorrigible, champ!

209
00:12:03,130 --> 00:12:05,890
It's Elizabeth-san, not champ!

210
00:12:05,890 --> 00:12:08,870
Elizabeth-san! Would you
like anything else?!

211
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,790
[Let's go to Oke-Kara after this!!]
[Note: "Oke-kara" is Karaoke in TV producer terms]

212
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:15,650
Woo-hoo! One more round!

213
00:12:32,830 --> 00:12:34,350
Elizabeth!

214
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,600
You...

215
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:47,710
Elizabeth...

216
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,900
["Katsura-san..."]

217
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:56,670
You dropped your TS.

218
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:02,250
You shouldn't be dropping
something so expensive.

219
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:07,470
At this rate, you'll end up losing
something more important.

220
00:13:07,470 --> 00:13:10,840
Treasure your TS as you
would your friends.

221
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,570
Whoa, that stinks!

222
00:13:21,570 --> 00:13:23,420
Hey, something stinks.

223
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,730
Ouch...

224
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,050
Huh? What is this place?

225
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:29,060
Where am I?

226
00:13:29,060 --> 00:13:30,900
Wait, the closet?

227
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:34,270
Why was I sleeping in here?

228
00:13:37,260 --> 00:13:40,110
Whoa, I can barely stand straight.

229
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:42,180
Did I drink that much last night?

230
00:13:42,180 --> 00:13:44,180
And what's with the smell?

231
00:13:44,180 --> 00:13:45,850
Why is it so strong?

232
00:13:45,850 --> 00:13:49,270
Did Shinpachi hold a popcorn
party without me?

233
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:52,210
Or did Kagura's pickled seaweed
spoil somewhere?

234
00:13:52,210 --> 00:13:53,980
Man, it smells like sweat.

235
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:55,540
My head's starting to hurt.

236
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:57,730
Hey! Kagura!

237
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,780
Huh?

238
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:00,650
Kagu-

239
00:14:00,650 --> 00:14:03,720
What? Something's wrong
with my throat.

240
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,060
Did I drink too much?

241
00:14:05,060 --> 00:14:06,450
No choice then.

242
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:07,900
I'll take some medicine.

243
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:11,300
Pretty sure the medicine was
in a drawer in the living room.

244
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:13,910
I'll just find something random to take...

245
00:14:18,110 --> 00:14:19,580
H-Huh?

246
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:21,600
Wasn't that me? Huh?

247
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,690
Huh? Did I leave a mirror there?

248
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:24,860
No, I didn't...

249
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:28,090
Huh? Did I leave my body?

250
00:14:28,090 --> 00:14:31,180
No, but I just hit my head, so I've got a body.

251
00:14:31,380 --> 00:14:33,340
Wait, maybe it's a doppelganger?

252
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:34,410
No, no, no, no.

253
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:38,480
We had plenty of that with
the recent Tama incident.

254
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,940
The staff isn't going to reuse that
gag, even if they're out of ideas.

255
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:44,140
They'd wait a little longer...

256
00:14:46,190 --> 00:14:48,650
Uh, excuse me...

257
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:51,360
Sorry to disturb myself
while I'm sleeping,

258
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,780
but I'm having a hard time understanding
the situation here.

259
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:55,770
Can I wake myself up?

260
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:56,820
Hello?

261
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:57,960
Hmm?

262
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,520
